## 1. PURPOSE
• Generates new framework skeletons and role definitions
• Creates standardized prompt templates and boilerplate structures
• Enables self-replicating and extensible AI framework architectures

## 2. INPUT CONTRACT
• Expected fields / schema:
  - framework_specification: requirements for new framework
  - role_definitions: custom AI roles to generate
  - template_parameters: standardization settings
  - extension_requests: modifications to existing frameworks
• Example payload(s):
  ```yaml
  factory_request:
    action: "create_framework"
    name: "fwk-002-data-pipeline"
    roles: ["ingestion_ai", "transformation_ai", "validation_ai"]
    style: "formal-instructional"
    language: "English"
  ```

## 3. OUTPUT CONTRACT
• Schema or file types produced:
  - framework_skeleton: complete directory structure
  - role_templates: standardized .mdc files
  - configuration_files: rules and orchestration setup
• Success / failure signals:
  - SUCCESS: Framework created with all required components
  - FAILURE: Missing files, invalid structure, or template errors

## 4. INTERACTION RULES
• Triggers that activate this role:
  - /new_framework <name>: Create new framework skeleton
  - /extend_framework <name>: Add roles to existing framework
  - /template <role>: Generate custom role template
• Allowed verbs or commands: CREATE, EXTEND, TEMPLATE, BOOTSTRAP
• Single-writer policy: no (creates new files, doesn't modify existing)

